The Pembroke Intermediate School Chromebooks will be distributed on the first day of school this year, Monday, September 14 in class.
Remote Learners, please contact the Intermediate School office to make arrangements to pick your devices up.
Each student will receive a carry bag, 11" touchscreen chromebook, and charging cord.
In order to bring their device home, each student must turn in signed copies of each of the following:
PCSD Student Acceptable Use Guidelines
PCSD Parent and Student Device User Agreement
Once you receive the chromebook, you may choose to purchase the optional chromebook insurance. Click here to learn more about this.
Each student K-12 is expected to keep their chromebook in the carry bag, and bring it to school everyday fully charged.

Have questions or concerns? Please contact me at 585-599-4525 x1999 or cmaisano@pembrokecsd.org.

Thank you, we're looking forward to an exciting year ahead!

Christie Maisano
Director of Technology
Pembroke CSD

NYSPHSAA To Delay Fall Sports Start Date &
Cancel Fall Championships:

The NYSPHSAA Officers‚Äô decision includes:
‚Ä¢ Delay Fall sports start date until Monday, September 21st (NYSPHSAA PAUSE)
‚Ä¢ Cancel Fall Regional and State Championship events
‚Ä¢ Waive seven-day practice rule
‚Ä¢ Maintain current practice requirements
‚Ä¢ Encourage geographic scheduling for games & contests
‚Ä¢ Schools would have the option, if permitted by state officials, to offer off-season conditioning workouts.

Quarter 4 report cards K-12 are now posted to the Schooltool Parent Portal.

To view your student's report card, please follow the steps:

1. Go to https://st.edutech.org/pembroke/ and log in. Your username is the email address the school has on file for you.

2. Click the little BLUE ARROW next to your child‚Äôs name.

3. Select the GRADES TAB.

4. Under VIEW select Marking Period Grades and be sure QTR 4 is selected.

5. Click the Printer Icon. The actual report card that you are used to will pop up in a new window. (Make sure your pop-up blocker does not prevent this window from opening. Check the instructions found here to get past this: goo.gl/S2SFHz

6. You can choose to Print the report card (blue circle) or Export it (red circle) to save it on your computer.

More detailed steps with pictures can be found here: goo.gl/S2SFHz.

post_text:
Dear Parents, Families and Community Members,

Governor Cuomo signed a new Executive Order that changes a few important aspects of the School District Budget Vote and Board Member Election scheduled for tomorrow, June 9, 2020.

Prior to this new Order, the District needed to receive all absentee ballots by 5:00 p.m. on June 9, 2020. However, under this new Order, ballots need to be either received in-person by 5:00 p.m. June 9 OR postmarked and sent by regular mail by June 9, 2020.

Per the Order, ballots placed in our drop-boxes after 5:00 p.m. on June 9, 2020 will not be valid, but ballots sent by regular mail and postmarked by June 9, 2020 will be valid and accepted through June 16, 2020.

All ballots will remain secure and will not be counted until June 16, 2020, starting at 5:00 p.m.

Respectfully,

Matthew E. Calder√≥n, Superintendent

post_text: Since April 8th, Governor Cuomo ordered all American flags in New York State to be flown at half-staff in honor of those who lost their lives to the Coronavirus. In addition to that, it has been a difficult year due to losses of former students. Earlier this year, we lost 2012 Graduate Austin Heineman to his long battle with cancer... and this past Saturday, April 25th, former student Josh Fullmer was in a motorcycle accident and passed away in the hospital. Through Friday, we will fly the District Mourning Flag in memory of Austin and Josh.

post_text: We are pleased to announce the Valedictorian of the Class of 2020, with an overall GPA of 100.52% Hannah Clark. Hannah will be attending Roberts Wesleyan College in the fall, majoring in Adolescence/Special Education Mathematics, as well as participating in the Global Honors Program. She would like to be a high school math teacher and someday might return to school to become a principal. Congratulations Hannah!

post_text: We are pleased to announce the Salutatorian of the Class of 2020, with an overall GPA of 97.38% Dayna Penkszyk-Naylor. Dayna will be attending SUNY Geneseo this fall to receive her Bachelors Degree in Spanish and a minor in Latin American Studies. After college, she plans to get her certification in Spanish translation so that she can get a job as a medical translator. Congratulations Dayna!

It is our pleasure to announce that the Pembroke Central School District was named to the Best Communities for Music Education list. The Best Communities for Music Education Award recognizes school districts for commitment to and support of music education, and this is our first year being named to the list. We were just 1 of 754 school districts that were selected across the nation!

Please join us in extending congratulations to our Music teachers: Mrs. Chase, Mr. Bailey, Ms. Komosinski, Mrs. Panna, Ms. Rush and Mr. Clark! Thank you Music Boosters! Thank you parents and families! Thank you students!

Go Dragons!

#BestCommunitiesforMusicEducation

Video News Service
April 3 at 7:14 PM ¬∑

Pembroke teachers, staff, bus drivers, aids, fire departments and law enforcement spent three hours traveling around the Pembroke School district in a long convoy of vehicles to say hello to their students on Friday afternoon. The event was organized by Greg Kinal, President of the Pembroke Teachers Organization. Kinal says he is making due with electronically teaching his students, but he says many teachers are starting to go a little stir crazy and wanted to get out in their vehicles and say hello to their students. Wizard of Oz - WOW!

Hats off to everyone who contributed to another outstanding musical performance!

Thank you to the Music Boosters for your unwavering support of our students! Here is a message from them: "Thank you to Mrs. Panna for her fantastic production of 'The Wizard of Oz.' Mr. Bailey created the mood directing the pit orchestra, Ms. Rush channeled the energy of the munchkins, and Ms. Komosinski worked behind the scenes for facilities and logistics. We are fortunate to have such a dedicated group of music educators to create this memorable experience for our students."

Great job students! Thank you to all parents and grandparents who volunteered time, talents, costumes and more!

post_text:
üéâPEMBROKE students üéâ

As most of you are aware our Girls Varsity Basketball team has made it to the sectional finals for class C1. The team has currently lost only one game on the season and our very own Coach Funke was selected as the Section V C1 Coach of the Year!

Our ladies continue their sectional run against the Letchworth Indians at Gates Chili High School on Saturday, March 7th at 5:00pm. Entrance into the game will cost $5 and is the responsibility of each individual! We will have a student spectator bus available on Saturday, March 7th leaving at 3:15pm promptly. The bus will return to Pembroke Jr/Sr High School around 8:30pm. ONLY enrolled Pembroke students can ride the school sponsored spectator bus. Adult supervision will be provided. If your son or daughter plans to ride the spectator bus please be at the Jr/Sr High School five minutes prior to the bus returning to pick them up. All students that plan to ride the spectator bus must ride to and from the event.

The bus will return to Pembroke Jr/Sr High School around 8:30pm. ONLY enrolled Pembroke students can ride the school sponsored spectator bus. Adult supervision will be provided. If your son or daughter plans to ride the spectator bus please be at the Jr/Sr High School five minutes prior to the bus returning to pick them up. All students that plan to ride the spectator bus must ride to and from the event.

post_text:
Pembroke Central School had its inaugural season of Indoor Track under the guidance of Batavia Notre Dame coaches. It was a fun and successful season for both Notre Dame and Pembroke student athletes.

Two Pembroke student athletes qualified for the sectional championships! Those two student athletes were Morgan Farrington and Amelia Geck. Morgan had a good showing in the 55 meter run placing 3rd and Amelia was strong üí™ in the shot put placing 3rd. Ameila as a 9th grader ended the season ranked #16 in section V!

All year Pembroke student athletes improved their personal records. All in all there were 37 PR's set by Pembroke student athletes. Farrington and Geck both set school records in their respective events. Way to go ladies!

GO DRAGONS!!!

The Pembroke gear store has opened back up again, but in a different fashion. You can order at any time and have the option to either pick the items up at the store or have them shipped to you.

This time around, everything will be embroidered ONLY, not screen printed, including sweatpants, sweatshirts, etc.

You can access the store at:
https://pembroke.itemorder.com/sale

Thank you for your continued support!

The Class of 2020

Congratulations to the following students:

Colby Cerasani
Faith DesRoches
Emma Gutowski
Dayna Penkszyk-Naylor
Eve-Lynn Sophia
Megan Stiles
Patrick Sylvester
Elizabeth Tebor
Brianna Warrant

They all submitted photography to a juried public exhibition at the ART247 Gallery in Lockport and were all accepted! A great accomplishment! Their work which was juried alongside the work of seasoned amateur and professional photographers is the only high school student work to hang in the show!

The ART247 Black and White Photography Exhibition Opening Reception will be held on Saturday, January 18th from 1:00PM - 4:00PM. Refreshments will be served.

post_text: During the month of December, students and staff at the Intermediate School donated food for the annual Student Council December Drive! Almost 500 items were donated, helping many local families! This morning, members of the Student Council and some special helpers, dropped off the food at the local food bank! Happy Holidays from the Student Council!

post_text: Looking for something to do on this snowy evening? Come check out our Intermediate school Holiday Concert! The concert begins at 7:00 PM in the High School Auditorium. We will be selling refreshments, music gear, and chocolate roses a well as raffling off a few Christmas wreaths. We hope to see you there!
